708455f-a.text:
Fifth Avenue, west side, north from W. 28th Street as photographed from the opoosite side and to the south of same. To the left is the 5 story marble 2nd National Bank at No. 250 Fifth Ave. The Marble Collegiate Reformed Church is at the N. W. corner of W. 29th Street. Between these appears the banner of the Progressive (Bull Moose) Party. This was a three corner race between Theodore Roosevelt, Wm. H. Taft and Woodrow Wilson, with the latter winning.
1912
Gift of George H. Hehn
71 W. 35th Street

708453f-a.text:

About 1924.
Gift of E. M. Jenks.

708454f-a.text:
Fifth Avenue at S. E. corner of 28th Street.
This building built in 1883 was the first co-operative apartment
house in New York City.
It was demolished soon after this photograph was made.
February 1925.
